We only use these macros for primitive types. In the case of arg == nullptr, we throw an exception when the expected type is primitive (see line 230 above for the test). So I think arg can't be nullptr in these macros and we can simplify the code. Adding a CHECK in DO_FIRST_ARG will do the assert job.

